<subSubSection pageNumber="264" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="264">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="264">Note:</emphasis>
Bobrov stated &quot;Type in the Linnaean herbarium&quot; (rather than the far commoner, and ineffective, &quot;Type in London&quot;). 714.3 (LINN) is the only sheet there that can be associated with this name so this choice is accepted as the type. Steinberg (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="264">Webbia</emphasis>
25: 305. 1971) reproduced the protologue and treated the name as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="264">nomen ambiguum</emphasis>
(rather than as a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="264">nomen illegitimum).</emphasis>
Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="264">Taxon</emphasis>
41: 555. 1992) independently reached the same conclusion as Bobrov.
</paragraph>
